Key Match Events: Niclas Füllkrug scored the winning goal for Germany in the 85th minute.
Joey Veerman scored the opening goal for the Netherlands in the 4th minute.
Maximilian Mittelstädt scored the equalizer for Germany in the 11th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Germany coach Julian Nagelsmann included six new faces in the team and brought Toni Kroos back from international retirement.
Nagelsmann emphasized the need for a character test in the face of adversity for his players.
Post-Match Reflections: Julian Nagelsmann praised the variability and positional changes in the Dutch team's build-up play.
Nagelsmann considered the game a valuable analysis opportunity for the upcoming European Championship.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Peter Schilling’s 1980s hit 'Major Tom' was played as the official German goal-jingle for the first time.
Germany wore pink jerseys for the first time.
